From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 23:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add the GRX-019 fused_post_chain recording-smoke and gated real-pass
 opt-in arms with result writeback scaffold

Stacked on 0001..0026 + 0036 + 0037. This is the GRX-019 bridge-recording /
real-pass opt-in slice (the GRX-009 0008+0009+0010 layers merged into one patch
for the fused_post_chain pass). It is a bring-up gate, not a default enablement,
and it does not change the shipping fallback semantics.

- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: adds three per-pass opt-in settings
  that all default to false and are separate from
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/enabled:
  .../fused_post_chain/dispatch_recording_smoke (harness-only recording-smoke
  marker arm), .../fused_post_chain/dispatch_real_pass (the gated REAL fused
  pass arm), and .../fused_post_chain/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade (a
  harness-only forced-failure knob for the fallback red/green leg).
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h: declares the reserved fused real-pass arm
  flag RXGD_CAP_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS (bridge value 1 << 13) carried in
  RxGdCaps.flags. This reuses the existing flags field: the C ABI struct layout
  and RXGD_ABI_VERSION are unchanged.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp: try_create_session() sets
  RXGD_CAP_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS ONLY when the fused dispatch_real_pass
  opt-in is enabled, and clears RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64 ONLY when the harness-only
  fused real_pass_force_capability_downgrade knob is enabled. Because the fused
  runtime binding preflight does NOT check int64 (only the bridge dispatch
  eligibility does), the forced knob is caught one level later than the texture
  passes, at dispatch eligibility (unsupported_device).
  try_record_fused_post_chain() emits the distinctive
  RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS and _RECORD markers only when
  rxgd_record_pass returned RXGD_STATUS_OK, both gated under the harness-only
  dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in (GRX Wave 4 print gating).
- renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp fusion-first block: when
  try_record_fused_post_chain() returned true on the real-pass arm, the Rurix
  bridge has already dispatched the fused kernel INTO the LDR destination
  ID3D12Resource* resolved in patch 0037 (dst_color and the scaffold
  dst_luminance both point at the LDR dest). The result writeback SCAFFOLD prints
  a machine-readable RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK
  marker, then deliberately clears rurix_recorded_fused_post_chain so the FULL
  native Godot luminance_reduction + tonemap chain still runs as the
  continuation/backstop: the fused kernel covers only the LINEAR + linear_to_srgb
  tonemap subset with the luminance final level, the luminance/dst bindings are a
  scaffold (PASS_CONTRACT.md 3.4/5), and GPU math parity is still pending, so the
  native raster tonemap re-renders the frame and the rendered image can never
  change while the scaffold is in place.

The bridge fails closed on the real-pass arm: it runs the runtime binding
preflight, the dispatch eligibility gate, the per-slot kernel-binding-kind
conformance check, and the math-parity gate, and returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK
with a machine-readable RXGD_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming
the FIRST missing prerequisite; the real dispatch is only linked under the
test-only d3d12-recording-shim bridge feature, so the shipping feature-off bridge
fails closed with real_dispatch_path_not_linked even when every software gate
passes. This does not change RXGD_ABI_VERSION, does not enable the pass by
default (all four fused_post_chain per-pass settings still default to false),
does not flip real_gpu_pass to true by itself, and makes no visual,
measured-telemetry, GPU-timestamp, or performance claim by itself.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index dec0fc6..8acc87b 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -251,6 +251,37 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// RXGD_PASS_FUSED_POST_CHAIN, so the native chain keeps rendering in
 	// practice and no acceleration is claimed.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/enabled", false);
+	// GRX-019: harness-only Godot-runtime fused_post_chain bridge dispatch
+	// recording smoke opt-in (0008-level). Defaults to false; it only gates
+	// the module-side per-dispatch RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_*
+	// markers. The bridge record path itself is only linked when the loaded
+	// rurix_godot.dll is built with the test-only d3d12-recording-shim feature
+	// AND the dispatch_real_pass opt-in below armed the fail-closed real-pass
+	// gate. The default build/config never enables it and the shipping
+	// (feature-off) bridge still returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK for
+	// RXGD_PASS_FUSED_POST_CHAIN.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_recording_smoke", false);
+	// GRX-019: opt-in gated REAL fused_post_chain pass bring-up arm
+	// (0009-level). Defaults to false. Even when enabled the bridge runs its
+	// runtime binding preflight, dispatch eligibility, per-slot
+	// kernel-binding-kind conformance, and math-parity checks and keeps
+	// returning RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK (with a machine-readable
+	// RXGD_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming the first
+	// missing prerequisite) unless every check passes AND a runtime-mappable
+	// real dispatch path is linked (d3d12-recording-shim builds only); the
+	// shipping feature-off bridge fails closed with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked, so the native Godot chain keeps rendering.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_real_pass", false);
+	// GRX-019: harness-only forced-failure knob for the fused_post_chain
+	// fallback red/green leg. The fused b0 carries i64 dimension pairs so int64
+	// IS required, but the fused runtime binding preflight does NOT check it
+	// (only the bridge dispatch eligibility does); when enabled the module
+	// clears the shader-int64 capability it advertises to the bridge, so the
+	// bridge fused_post_chain dispatch eligibility fails closed with
+	// unsupported_device (one level later than the texture passes catch it)
+	// while the native Godot chain keeps rendering. Defaults to false; never
+	// enabled by the shipping build/config.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade", false);
 	// GRX-017 material_sorting telemetry (patch 0026, telemetry-only slice):
 	// default-false opt-in for the verbose-only per-interval
 	// RXGD_MATERIAL_SORTING_TELEMETRY line emitted by the Forward+ renderer
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index 4c73603..ddbabb9 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -306,6 +306,27 @@ void RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_create_session() {
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
 		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
 	}
+	// GRX-019: arm the opt-in gated REAL fused_post_chain pass attempt ONLY
+	// when the default-false fused_post_chain dispatch_real_pass opt-in is
+	// enabled. The bridge still fails closed (fallback +
+	// RXGD_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED first missing prerequisite)
+	// unless every gate passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path
+	// is linked and completes; this is a bring-up gate, not a default runtime
+	// pass.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_real_pass")) {
+		caps.flags |= RXGD_CAP_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS;
+	}
+	// GRX-019: harness-only fused_post_chain forced-failure knob. The fused b0
+	// carries i64 dimension pairs so int64 IS required, but the fused runtime
+	// binding preflight does NOT check it (only the bridge dispatch eligibility
+	// does); clearing the shader-int64 capability therefore makes the bridge
+	// fused_post_chain dispatch eligibility fail closed with unsupported_device
+	// (one level later than the texture passes catch it) while the native Godot
+	// chain keeps rendering. The fallback red/green leg of the GRX-019
+	// real-pass enablement smoke verifies exactly this.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
+		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
+	}
 	if (adapter_luid_valid) {
 		memcpy(caps.adapter_luid, &adapter_luid, sizeof(adapter_luid));
 	}
@@ -1006,6 +1027,19 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_fused_post_chain(uint64_t p_src_color_nati
 		}
 		return false;
 	}
+	// GRX-019: only reachable when the bridge's opt-in real-pass arm actually
+	// returned RXGD_STATUS_OK after a real recorded dispatch
+	// (d3d12-recording-shim builds only; the shipping feature-off bridge always
+	// falls back with real_dispatch_path_not_linked first). GRX Wave 4 print
+	// gating: both per-dispatch stdout markers are harness instrumentation and
+	// are gated under the harness-only dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in — the
+	// production dispatch_real_pass path emits zero per-dispatch stdout.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS: pass=RXGD_PASS_FUSED_POST_CHAIN dispatched=1");
+	}
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_FUSED_POST_CHAIN recorded=1");
+	}
 	return true;
 }
 
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
index 6e834c7..4f10772 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
@@ -90,6 +90,17 @@
 // diagnostic unless every check passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real
 // dispatch path is linked and completes.
 #define RXGD_CAP_CLUSTER_STORE_REAL_PASS 256u
+// GRX-019 opt-in fused_post_chain real-pass arm carried in RxGdCaps.flags
+// (ABI v1, no struct layout change; bridge value 1 << 13). Set only when the
+// default-false rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_real_pass
+// opt-in is enabled. Setting it never on its own makes the bridge return
+// RXGD_STATUS_OK: the fail-closed FusedPostChainGate runs preflight ->
+// eligibility -> binding-kind (texture2d x3 / rwtexture2d x2) -> math-parity
+// -> linked-dispatch checks and returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK with an
+// RXGD_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic unless every check
+// passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path is linked and
+// completes.
+#define RXGD_CAP_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS 8192u
 
 typedef struct RxGdCaps {
 	uint32_t abi_version;
diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
index d88c0fc..26eac79 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
@@ -963,6 +963,25 @@ void RendererSceneRenderRD::_render_buffers_post_process_and_tonemap(const Rende
 					// computed the real current). The gate only requires nonzero
 					// source dims.
 					rurix_recorded_fused_post_chain = D3D12Hooks::get_singleton()->try_record_fused_post_chain(rurix_fused_src_color, rurix_fused_lum, rurix_fused_lum, rurix_fused_dst_color, rurix_fused_dst_color, (uint32_t)MAX(color_size.x, 0), (uint32_t)MAX(color_size.y, 0), 1u, 1u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f, tonemap.exposure, tonemap.white, tonemap.luminance_multiplier, 0.0f, tonemap.auto_exposure_scale);
+					if (rurix_recorded_fused_post_chain) {
+						// GRX-019 result writeback SCAFFOLD. The Rurix bridge dispatched
+						// the fused kernel into the real LDR destination (dst_color) and
+						// the scaffold dst_luminance (also the LDR dest, fully overwritten
+						// below). Record that writeback with a machine-readable marker,
+						// then keep the FULL native Godot luminance_reduction + tonemap
+						// chain as the continuation/backstop: the fused kernel covers only
+						// the LINEAR + linear_to_srgb tonemap subset with the luminance
+						// final level, GPU math parity is still pending, and the
+						// luminance/dst bindings are a scaffold (3.4/5), so the native
+						// raster tonemap re-renders the frame and the image can never
+						// change while this scaffold is in place. GRX Wave 4 print gating:
+						// harness instrumentation only (dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in);
+						// zero per-dispatch stdout on the production path.
+						if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+							print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK: dst=tonemap_destination native_continuation=active scaffold=1");
+						}
+						rurix_recorded_fused_post_chain = false;
+					}
 				}
 			}
 			if (!rurix_recorded_fused_post_chain && D3D12Hooks::get_singleton() != nullptr && rurix_tonemap_dest_texture.is_valid()) {
-- 
